 111 @pytest.fixture(params=_any_string_method, ids=ids)
 112 def any_string_method(request):
 113     """
 114     Fixture for all public methods of `StringMethods`
 115 
 116     This fixture returns a tuple of the method name and sample arguments
 117     necessary to call the method.
 118 
 119     Returns
 120     -------
 121     method_name : str
 122         The name of the method in `StringMethods`
 123     args : tuple
 124         Sample values for the positional arguments
 125     kwargs : dict
 126         Sample values for the keyword arguments
 127 
 128     Examples
 129     --------
 130     >>> def test_something(any_string_method):
 131     ...     s = pd.Series(['a', 'b', np.nan, 'd'])
 132     ...
 133     ...     method_name, args, kwargs = any_string_method
 134     ...     method = getattr(s.str, method_name)
 135     ...     # will not raise
 136     ...     method(*args, **kwargs)
 137     """
 138     return request.param

 153 def any_allowed_skipna_inferred_dtype(request):
 154     """
 155     Fixture for all (inferred) dtypes allowed in StringMethods.__init__
 156 
 157     The covered (inferred) types are:
 158     * 'string'
 159     * 'empty'
 160     * 'bytes'
 161     * 'mixed'
 162     * 'mixed-integer'
 163 
 164     Returns
 165     -------
 166     inferred_dtype : str
 167         The string for the inferred dtype from _libs.lib.infer_dtype
 168     values : np.ndarray
 169         An array of object dtype that will be inferred to have
 170         `inferred_dtype`
 171 
 172     Examples
 173     --------
 174     >>> import pandas._libs.lib as lib
 175     >>>
 176     >>> def test_something(any_allowed_skipna_inferred_dtype):
 177     ...     inferred_dtype, values = any_allowed_skipna_inferred_dtype
 178     ...     # will pass
 179     ...     assert lib.infer_dtype(values, skipna=True) == inferred_dtype
 180     ...
 181     ...     # constructor for .str-accessor will also pass
 182     ...     pd.Series(values).str
 183     """
 184     inferred_dtype, values = request.param
 185     values = np.array(values, dtype=object)  # object dtype to avoid casting

 194         # GH 6106, GH 9322

 198     def test_api_mi_raises(self):
 199         # GH 23679
 200         mi = MultiIndex.from_arrays([["a", "b", "c"]])
 201         msg = "Can only use .str accessor with Index, not MultiIndex"
 202         with pytest.raises(AttributeError, match=msg):
 203             mi.str
 204         assert not hasattr(mi, "str")

 206     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [object, "category"])
 207     def test_api_per_dtype(self, index_or_series, dtype, any_skipna_inferred_dtype):
 208         # one instance of parametrized fixture
 209         box = index_or_series
 210         inferred_dtype, values = any_skipna_inferred_dtype
 211 
 212         t = box(values, dtype=dtype)  # explicit dtype to avoid casting
 213 
 214         types_passing_constructor = [
 215             "string",
 216             "unicode",
 217             "empty",
 218             "bytes",
 219             "mixed",
 220             "mixed-integer",
 221         ]
 222         if inferred_dtype in types_passing_constructor:
 223             # GH 6106
 224             assert isinstance(t.str, strings.StringMethods)
 225         else:
 226             # GH 9184, GH 23011, GH 23163
 227             msg = "Can only use .str accessor with string values.*"
 228             with pytest.raises(AttributeError, match=msg):
 229                 t.str
 230             assert not hasattr(t, "str")

 232     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [object, "category"])
 233     def test_api_per_method(
 234         self,
 235         index_or_series,
 236         dtype,
 237         any_allowed_skipna_inferred_dtype,
 238         any_string_method,
 239         request,
 240     ):
 241         # this test does not check correctness of the different methods,
 242         # just that the methods work on the specified (inferred) dtypes,
 243         # and raise on all others
 244         box = index_or_series
 245 
 246         # one instance of each parametrized fixture
 247         inferred_dtype, values = any_allowed_skipna_inferred_dtype
 248         method_name, args, kwargs = any_string_method
 249 
 250         # TODO: get rid of these xfails
 251         reason = None
 252         if box is Index and values.size == 0:
 253             if method_name in ["partition", "rpartition"] and kwargs.get(
 254                 "expand", True
 255             ):
 256                 reason = "Method cannot deal with empty Index"
 257             elif method_name == "split" and kwargs.get("expand", None):
 258                 reason = "Split fails on empty Series when expand=True"
 259             elif method_name == "get_dummies":
 260                 reason = "Need to fortify get_dummies corner cases"
 261 
 262         elif box is Index and inferred_dtype == "empty" and dtype == object:
 263             if method_name == "get_dummies":
 264                 reason = "Need to fortify get_dummies corner cases"
 265 
 266         if reason is not None:
 267             mark = pytest.mark.xfail(reason=reason)
 268             request.node.add_marker(mark)
 269 
 270         t = box(values, dtype=dtype)  # explicit dtype to avoid casting
 271         method = getattr(t.str, method_name)
 272 
 273         bytes_allowed = method_name in ["decode", "get", "len", "slice"]
 274         # as of v0.23.4, all methods except 'cat' are very lenient with the
 275         # allowed data types, just returning NaN for entries that error.
 276         # This could be changed with an 'errors'-kwarg to the `str`-accessor,
 277         # see discussion in GH 13877
 278         mixed_allowed = method_name not in ["cat"]
 279 
 280         allowed_types = (
 281             ["string", "unicode", "empty"]
 282             + ["bytes"] * bytes_allowed
 283             + ["mixed", "mixed-integer"] * mixed_allowed
 284         )
 285 
 286         if inferred_dtype in allowed_types:
 287             # xref GH 23555, GH 23556
 288             method(*args, **kwargs)  # works!
 289         else:
 290             # GH 23011, GH 23163
 291             msg = (
 292                 f"Cannot use .str.{method_name} with values of "
 293                 f"inferred dtype {repr(inferred_dtype)}."
 294             )
 295             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 296                 method(*args, **kwargs)
 297 
 298     def test_api_for_categorical(self, any_string_method):
 299         # https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/10661
 300         s = Series(list("aabb"))
 301         s = s + " " + s
 302         c = s.astype("category")
 303         assert isinstance(c.str, strings.StringMethods)
 304 
 305         method_name, args, kwargs = any_string_method
 306 
 307         result = getattr(c.str, method_name)(*args, **kwargs)
 308         expected = getattr(s.str, method_name)(*args, **kwargs)
 309 
 310         if isinstance(result, DataFrame):
 311             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
 312         elif isinstance(result, Series):
 313             tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 314         else:
 315             # str.cat(others=None) returns string, for example
 316             assert result == expected

 318     def test_iter(self):
 319         # GH3638
 320         strs = "google", "wikimedia", "wikipedia", "wikitravel"
 321         ds = Series(strs)
 322 
 323         with tm.assert_produces_warning(FutureWarning):
 324             for s in ds.str:
 325                 # iter must yield a Series
 326                 assert isinstance(s, Series)
 327 
 328                 # indices of each yielded Series should be equal to the index of
 329                 # the original Series
 330                 tm.assert_index_equal(s.index, ds.index)
 331 
 332                 for el in s:
 333                     # each element of the series is either a basestring/str or nan
 334                     assert isinstance(el, str) or isna(el)
 335 
 336         # desired behavior is to iterate until everything would be nan on the
 337         # next iter so make sure the last element of the iterator was 'l' in
 338         # this case since 'wikitravel' is the longest string
 339         assert s.dropna().values.item() == "l"

 377     @pytest.mark.parametrize("other", [None, Series, Index])
 378     def test_str_cat_name(self, index_or_series, other):
 379         # GH 21053
 380         box = index_or_series
 381         values = ["a", "b"]
 382         if other:
 383             other = other(values)
 384         else:

 389     def test_str_cat(self, index_or_series):
 390         box = index_or_series
 391         # test_cat above tests "str_cat" from ndarray;
 392         # here testing "str.cat" from Series/Indext to ndarray/list
 393         s = box(["a", "a", "b", "b", "c", np.nan])
 394 
 395         # single array
 396         result = s.str.cat()
 397         expected = "aabbc"
 398         assert result == expected
 399 
 400         result = s.str.cat(na_rep="-")
 401         expected = "aabbc-"
 402         assert result == expected
 403 
 404         result = s.str.cat(sep="_", na_rep="NA")
 405         expected = "a_a_b_b_c_NA"
 406         assert result == expected
 407 
 408         t = np.array(["a", np.nan, "b", "d", "foo", np.nan], dtype=object)
 409         expected = box(["aa", "a-", "bb", "bd", "cfoo", "--"])
 410 
 411         # Series/Index with array
 412         result = s.str.cat(t, na_rep="-")
 413         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 414 
 415         # Series/Index with list
 416         result = s.str.cat(list(t), na_rep="-")
 417         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 418 
 419         # errors for incorrect lengths
 420         rgx = r"If `others` contains arrays or lists \(or other list-likes.*"
 421         z = Series(["1", "2", "3"])
 422 
 423         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 424             s.str.cat(z.values)
 425 
 426         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 427             s.str.cat(list(z))

 429     def test_str_cat_raises_intuitive_error(self, index_or_series):
 430         # GH 11334
 431         box = index_or_series
 432         s = box(["a", "b", "c", "d"])
 433         message = "Did you mean to supply a `sep` keyword?"
 434         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=message):
 435             s.str.cat("|")
 436         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=message):
 437             s.str.cat("    ")

 439     @pytest.mark.parametrize("sep", ["", None])
 440     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype_target", ["object", "category"])
 441     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype_caller", ["object", "category"])
 442     def test_str_cat_categorical(
 443         self, index_or_series, dtype_caller, dtype_target, sep
 444     ):
 445         box = index_or_series
 446 
 447         s = Index(["a", "a", "b", "a"], dtype=dtype_caller)
 448         s = s if box == Index else Series(s, index=s)
 449         t = Index(["b", "a", "b", "c"], dtype=dtype_target)
 450 
 451         expected = Index(["ab", "aa", "bb", "ac"])
 452         expected = expected if box == Index else Series(expected, index=s)
 453 
 454         # Series/Index with unaligned Index -> t.values
 455         result = s.str.cat(t.values, sep=sep)
 456         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 457 
 458         # Series/Index with Series having matching Index
 459         t = Series(t.values, index=s)
 460         result = s.str.cat(t, sep=sep)
 461         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 462 
 463         # Series/Index with Series.values
 464         result = s.str.cat(t.values, sep=sep)
 465         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 466 
 467         # Series/Index with Series having different Index
 468         t = Series(t.values, index=t.values)
 469         expected = Index(["aa", "aa", "aa", "bb", "bb"])
 470         expected = (
 471             expected if box == Index else Series(expected, index=expected.str[:1])
 472         )
 473 
 474         result = s.str.cat(t, sep=sep)
 475         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)

 477     # test integer/float dtypes (inferred by constructor) and mixed
 478     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 479         "data",
 480         [[1, 2, 3], [0.1, 0.2, 0.3], [1, 2, "b"]],
 481         ids=["integers", "floats", "mixed"],
 482     )
 483     # without dtype=object, np.array would cast [1, 2, 'b'] to ['1', '2', 'b']
 484     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 485         "box",
 486         [Series, Index, list, lambda x: np.array(x, dtype=object)],
 487         ids=["Series", "Index", "list", "np.array"],
 488     )
 489     def test_str_cat_wrong_dtype_raises(self, box, data):
 490         # GH 22722
 491         s = Series(["a", "b", "c"])
 492         t = box(data)
 493 
 494         msg = "Concatenation requires list-likes containing only strings.*"
 495         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 496             # need to use outer and na_rep, as otherwise Index would not raise
 497             s.str.cat(t, join="outer", na_rep="-")

 499     def test_str_cat_mixed_inputs(self, index_or_series):
 500         box = index_or_series
 501         s = Index(["a", "b", "c", "d"])
 502         s = s if box == Index else Series(s, index=s)
 503 
 504         t = Series(["A", "B", "C", "D"], index=s.values)
 505         d = concat([t, Series(s, index=s)], axis=1)
 506 
 507         expected = Index(["aAa", "bBb", "cCc", "dDd"])
 508         expected = expected if box == Index else Series(expected.values, index=s.values)
 509 
 510         # Series/Index with DataFrame
 511         result = s.str.cat(d)
 512         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 513 
 514         # Series/Index with two-dimensional ndarray
 515         result = s.str.cat(d.values)
 516         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 517 
 518         # Series/Index with list of Series
 519         result = s.str.cat([t, s])
 520         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 521 
 522         # Series/Index with mixed list of Series/array
 523         result = s.str.cat([t, s.values])
 524         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 525 
 526         # Series/Index with list of Series; different indexes
 527         t.index = ["b", "c", "d", "a"]
 528         expected = box(["aDa", "bAb", "cBc", "dCd"])
 529         expected = expected if box == Index else Series(expected.values, index=s.values)
 530         result = s.str.cat([t, s])
 531         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 532 
 533         # Series/Index with mixed list; different index
 534         result = s.str.cat([t, s.values])
 535         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 536 
 537         # Series/Index with DataFrame; different indexes
 538         d.index = ["b", "c", "d", "a"]
 539         expected = box(["aDd", "bAa", "cBb", "dCc"])
 540         expected = expected if box == Index else Series(expected.values, index=s.values)
 541         result = s.str.cat(d)
 542         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)
 543 
 544         # errors for incorrect lengths
 545         rgx = r"If `others` contains arrays or lists \(or other list-likes.*"
 546         z = Series(["1", "2", "3"])
 547         e = concat([z, z], axis=1)
 548 
 549         # two-dimensional ndarray
 550         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 551             s.str.cat(e.values)
 552 
 553         # list of list-likes
 554         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 555             s.str.cat([z.values, s.values])
 556 
 557         # mixed list of Series/list-like
 558         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 559             s.str.cat([z.values, s])
 560 
 561         # errors for incorrect arguments in list-like
 562         rgx = "others must be Series, Index, DataFrame,.*"
 563         # make sure None/NaN do not crash checks in _get_series_list
 564         u = Series(["a", np.nan, "c", None])
 565 
 566         # mix of string and Series
 567         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 568             s.str.cat([u, "u"])
 569 
 570         # DataFrame in list
 571         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 572             s.str.cat([u, d])
 573 
 574         # 2-dim ndarray in list
 575         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 576             s.str.cat([u, d.values])
 577 
 578         # nested lists
 579         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 580             s.str.cat([u, [u, d]])
 581 
 582         # forbidden input type: set
 583         # GH 23009
 584         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 585             s.str.cat(set(u))
 586 
 587         # forbidden input type: set in list
 588         # GH 23009
 589         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 590             s.str.cat([u, set(u)])
 591 
 592         # other forbidden input type, e.g. int
 593         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 594             s.str.cat(1)
 595 
 596         # nested list-likes
 597         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=rgx):
 598             s.str.cat(iter([t.values, list(s)]))

 600     @pytest.mark.parametrize("join", ["left", "outer", "inner", "right"])
 601     def test_str_cat_align_indexed(self, index_or_series, join):
 602         # https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/18657
 603         box = index_or_series
 604 
 605         s = Series(["a", "b", "c", "d"], index=["a", "b", "c", "d"])
 606         t = Series(["D", "A", "E", "B"], index=["d", "a", "e", "b"])
 607         sa, ta = s.align(t, join=join)
 608         # result after manual alignment of inputs
 609         expected = sa.str.cat(ta, na_rep="-")
 610 
 611         if box == Index:
 612             s = Index(s)
 613             sa = Index(sa)
 614             expected = Index(expected)
 615 
 616         result = s.str.cat(t, join=join, na_rep="-")
 617         assert_series_or_index_equal(result, expected)

 619     @pytest.mark.parametrize("join", ["left", "outer", "inner", "right"])
 620     def test_str_cat_align_mixed_inputs(self, join):
 621         s = Series(["a", "b", "c", "d"])
 622         t = Series(["d", "a", "e", "b"], index=[3, 0, 4, 1])
 623         d = concat([t, t], axis=1)
 624 
 625         expected_outer = Series(["aaa", "bbb", "c--", "ddd", "-ee"])
 626         expected = expected_outer.loc[s.index.join(t.index, how=join)]
 627 
 628         # list of Series
 629         result = s.str.cat([t, t], join=join, na_rep="-")
 630         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 631 
 632         # DataFrame
 633         result = s.str.cat(d, join=join, na_rep="-")
 634         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 635 
 636         # mixed list of indexed/unindexed
 637         u = np.array(["A", "B", "C", "D"])
 638         expected_outer = Series(["aaA", "bbB", "c-C", "ddD", "-e-"])
 639         # joint index of rhs [t, u]; u will be forced have index of s
 640         rhs_idx = t.index & s.index if join == "inner" else t.index | s.index
 641 
 642         expected = expected_outer.loc[s.index.join(rhs_idx, how=join)]
 643         result = s.str.cat([t, u], join=join, na_rep="-")
 644         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 645 
 646         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match="others must be Series,.*"):
 647             # nested lists are forbidden
 648             s.str.cat([t, list(u)], join=join)
 649 
 650         # errors for incorrect lengths
 651         rgx = r"If `others` contains arrays or lists \(or other list-likes.*"
 652         z = Series(["1", "2", "3"]).values
 653 
 654         # unindexed object of wrong length
 655         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 656             s.str.cat(z, join=join)
 657 
 658         # unindexed object of wrong length in list
 659         with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=rgx):
 660             s.str.cat([t, z], join=join)

 662     def test_str_cat_all_na(self, index_or_series, index_or_series2):
 663         # GH 24044
 664         box = index_or_series
 665         other = index_or_series2
 666 
 667         # check that all NaNs in caller / target work
 668         s = Index(["a", "b", "c", "d"])

 791         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(rs, xp)
 792

 794         xp = Series(
 795             [False, np.nan, False, np.nan, np.nan, True, np.nan, np.nan, np.nan]
 796         )
 797         assert isinstance(rs, Series)
 798         tm.assert_series_equal(rs, xp)

 801         values = np.array(["foo", np.nan, "fooommm__foo", "mmm_"], dtype=np.object_)
 802         pat = "mmm[_]+"
 803 
 804         result = strings.str_contains(values, pat)

 806         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 807

1090             result = values.str.replace(pat, "", case=True)

1695     def test_extractall_no_matches(self, data, names):
1696         # GH19075 extractall with no matches should return a valid MultiIndex
1697         n = len(data)
1698         if len(names) == 1:
1699             i = Index(range(n), name=names[0])
1700         else:
1701             a = (tuple([i] * (n - 1)) for i in range(n))
1702             i = MultiIndex.from_tuples(a, names=names)
1703         s = Series(data, name="series_name", index=i, dtype="object")
1704         ei = MultiIndex.from_tuples([], names=(names + ("match",)))
1705

1708         e = DataFrame(columns=[0], index=ei)
1709         tm.assert_frame_equal(r, e)
1710 
1711         # two un-named groups.
1712         r = s.str.extractall("(z)(z)")
1713         e = DataFrame(columns=[0, 1], index=ei)
1714         tm.assert_frame_equal(r, e)
1715 
1716         # one named group.
1717         r = s.str.extractall("(?P<first>z)")
1718         e = DataFrame(columns=["first"], index=ei)
1719         tm.assert_frame_equal(r, e)
1720 
1721         # two named groups.
1722         r = s.str.extractall("(?P<first>z)(?P<second>z)")
1723         e = DataFrame(columns=["first", "second"], index=ei)
1724         tm.assert_frame_equal(r, e)
1725 
1726         # one named, one un-named.
1727         r = s.str.extractall("(z)(?P<second>z)")
1728         e = DataFrame(columns=[0, "second"], index=ei)
1729         tm.assert_frame_equal(r, e)

2784     def test_partition_series(self):
2785         # https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/issues/23558
2786 
2787         values = Series(["a_b_c", "c_d_e", np.nan, "f_g_h", None])
2788 
2789         result = values.str.partition("_", expand=False)
2790         exp = Series(
2791             [("a", "_", "b_c"), ("c", "_", "d_e"), np.nan, ("f", "_", "g_h"), None]
2792         )
2793         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2794 
2795         result = values.str.rpartition("_", expand=False)
2796         exp = Series(
2797             [("a_b", "_", "c"), ("c_d", "_", "e"), np.nan, ("f_g", "_", "h"), None]
2798         )
2799         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2800 
2801         # more than one char
2802         values = Series(["a__b__c", "c__d__e", np.nan, "f__g__h", None])
2803         result = values.str.partition("__", expand=False)
2804         exp = Series(
2805             [
2806                 ("a", "__", "b__c"),
2807                 ("c", "__", "d__e"),
2808                 np.nan,
2809                 ("f", "__", "g__h"),
2810                 None,
2811             ]
2812         )
2813         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2814 
2815         result = values.str.rpartition("__", expand=False)
2816         exp = Series(
2817             [
2818                 ("a__b", "__", "c"),
2819                 ("c__d", "__", "e"),
2820                 np.nan,
2821                 ("f__g", "__", "h"),
2822                 None,
2823             ]
2824         )
2825         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2826 
2827         # None
2828         values = Series(["a b c", "c d e", np.nan, "f g h", None])
2829         result = values.str.partition(expand=False)
2830         exp = Series(
2831             [("a", " ", "b c"), ("c", " ", "d e"), np.nan, ("f", " ", "g h"), None]
2832         )
2833         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2834 
2835         result = values.str.rpartition(expand=False)
2836         exp = Series(
2837             [("a b", " ", "c"), ("c d", " ", "e"), np.nan, ("f g", " ", "h"), None]
2838         )
2839         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2840 
2841         # Not split
2842         values = Series(["abc", "cde", np.nan, "fgh", None])
2843         result = values.str.partition("_", expand=False)
2844         exp = Series([("abc", "", ""), ("cde", "", ""), np.nan, ("fgh", "", ""), None])
2845         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2846 
2847         result = values.str.rpartition("_", expand=False)
2848         exp = Series([("", "", "abc"), ("", "", "cde"), np.nan, ("", "", "fgh"), None])
2849         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2850 
2851         # unicode
2852         values = Series(["a_b_c", "c_d_e", np.nan, "f_g_h"])
2853 
2854         result = values.str.partition("_", expand=False)
2855         exp = Series([("a", "_", "b_c"), ("c", "_", "d_e"), np.nan, ("f", "_", "g_h")])
2856         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2857 
2858         result = values.str.rpartition("_", expand=False)
2859         exp = Series([("a_b", "_", "c"), ("c_d", "_", "e"), np.nan, ("f_g", "_", "h")])
2860         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
2861 
2862         # compare to standard lib
2863         values = Series(["A_B_C", "B_C_D", "E_F_G", "EFGHEF"])
2864         result = values.str.partition("_", expand=False).tolist()
2865         assert result == [v.partition("_") for v in values]
2866         result = values.str.rpartition("_", expand=False).tolist()
2867         assert result == [v.rpartition("_") for v in values]

3466     def test_index_str_accessor_visibility(self):
3467         from pandas.core.strings import StringMethods
3468 
3469         cases = [
3470             (["a", "b"], "string"),
3471             (["a", "b", 1], "mixed-integer"),
3472             (["a", "b", 1.3], "mixed"),
3473             (["a", "b", 1.3, 1], "mixed-integer"),
3474             (["aa", datetime(2011, 1, 1)], "mixed"),
3475         ]
3476         for values, tp in cases:
3477             idx = Index(values)
3478             assert isinstance(Series(values).str, StringMethods)
3479             assert isinstance(idx.str, StringMethods)
3480             assert idx.inferred_type == tp
3481 
3482         for values, tp in cases:
3483             idx = Index(values)
3484             assert isinstance(Series(values).str, StringMethods)
3485             assert isinstance(idx.str, StringMethods)
3486             assert idx.inferred_type == tp
3487 
3488         cases = [
3489             ([1, np.nan], "floating"),
3490             ([datetime(2011, 1, 1)], "datetime64"),
3491             ([timedelta(1)], "timedelta64"),
3492         ]
3493         for values, tp in cases:
3494             idx = Index(values)
3495             message = "Can only use .str accessor with string values"
3496             with pytest.raises(AttributeError, match=message):
3497                 Series(values).str
3498             with pytest.raises(AttributeError, match=message):
3499                 idx.str
3500             assert idx.inferred_type == tp
3501 
3502         # MultiIndex has mixed dtype, but not allow to use accessor
3503         idx = MultiIndex.from_tuples([("a", "b"), ("a", "b")])
3504         assert idx.inferred_type == "mixed"
3505         message = "Can only use .str accessor with Index, not MultiIndex"

3530 def test_string_array(any_string_method):
3531     method_name, args, kwargs = any_string_method
3532     if method_name == "decode":
3533         pytest.skip("decode requires bytes.")
3534 
3535     data = ["a", "bb", np.nan, "ccc"]
3536     a = Series(data, dtype=object)
3537     b = Series(data, dtype="string")
3538

3540     result = getattr(b.str, method_name)(*args, **kwargs)
3541 
3542     if isinstance(expected, Series):
3543         if expected.dtype == "object" and lib.is_string_array(
3544             expected.dropna().values,
3545         ):
3546             assert result.dtype == "string"
3547             result = result.astype(object)
3548 
3549         elif expected.dtype == "object" and lib.is_bool_array(
3550             expected.values, skipna=True
3551         ):
3552             assert result.dtype == "boolean"
3553             result = result.astype(object)
3554 
3555         elif expected.dtype == "float" and expected.isna().any():
3556             assert result.dtype == "Int64"
3557             result = result.astype("float")
3558 
3559     elif isinstance(expected, DataFrame):
3560         columns = expected.select_dtypes(include="object").columns
3561         assert all(result[columns].dtypes == "string")
3562         result[columns] = result[columns].astype(object)
